    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3862139967" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3862139967" />
    <a title="Kathy Golden" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/10891080-kathy-golden"><img alt="Kathy Golden" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1379129603p2/10891080.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3862139967?book_show_action=true">Feb 26, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kathy Golden" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kathy Golden" href="/user/show/10891080-kathy-golden">Kathy Golden</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Mass Market Paperback 9780061491900" href="/book/show/9571478-just-like-heaven">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3862139967" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer729579941942679138"><a href='https://www.amazon.com/Just-Like-Heaven-Smythe-Smith-Quartet-ebook/dp/B004FEF6FG?&amp;linkCode=li3&amp;tag=publandread-20&amp;linkId=4f2705d427fd8e7fa0124922622326e4&amp;language=en_US&amp;ref_=as_li_ss_il' target='_blank' rel='nofollow noopener'>
  <img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1614406050i/30931524.jpg' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/>
</a><span>[image error]</span> <a target='_blank' href='https://www.amazon.com/Just-Like-Heaven-Smythe-Smith-Quartet-ebook/dp/B004FEF6FG?&amp;_encoding=UTF8&amp;tag=publandread-20&amp;linkCode=ur2&amp;linkId=0b251dff04f1d9efec9c0a6af90cbb18&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325' rel='nofollow noopener'>Just Like Heaven</a> is written in 3rd person, with both POVs. POV changes with the start of new chapters, though I don&apos;t think the chapter breaks always indicate a change in POV. <br/><br/>The beginning part of the story starts out with the main MCs as children. It&apos;s a cool and enjoyable beginning. My favorite part of the book takes place during this time. The middle part was unbelievably slow. The events taking place should have been more engaging, but there were too many overlong sentence</span>
  <span id="freeText729579941942679138" style="display:none"><a href="https://www.amazon.com/Just-Like-Heaven-Smythe-Smith-Quartet-ebook/dp/B004FEF6FG?&amp;linkCode=li3&amp;tag=publandread-20&amp;linkId=4f2705d427fd8e7fa0124922622326e4&amp;language=en_US&amp;ref_=as_li_ss_il" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener">
  <img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1614406050i/30931524.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg">
</a><span>[image error]</span> <a target="_blank" href="https://www.amazon.com/Just-Like-Heaven-Smythe-Smith-Quartet-ebook/dp/B004FEF6FG?&amp;_encoding=UTF8&amp;tag=publandread-20&amp;linkCode=ur2&amp;linkId=0b251dff04f1d9efec9c0a6af90cbb18&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=9325" rel="nofollow noopener">Just Like Heaven</a> is written in 3rd person, with both POVs. POV changes with the start of new chapters, though I don't think the chapter breaks always indicate a change in POV. <br><br>The beginning part of the story starts out with the main MCs as children. It's a cool and enjoyable beginning. My favorite part of the book takes place during this time. The middle part was unbelievably slow. The events taking place should have been more engaging, but there were too many overlong sentences, with addendums attached to practically every single action and thought. That part of the book was slow enough to cause me to quit. But I kept reading because I really liked Marcus and Honoria and because the author possessed the ability to take these two characters from friends to lovers in the most believable of ways. Readers can feel these two gradually waking up and seeing each other differently, even though they are not yet aware they are falling in love. Another thing--maybe the main thing--that kept me reading was listening to the audiobook. Rosalyn Landor's narration of this story is like listening to a full-cast production. Her ability to perform so many different female voices is brilliant. <br><br>So my final thoughts: If that gastropod-like middle makes you feel like you can't finish, just skip ahead to Chapter 15, where some tension is added and the pace picks up. You can always double-back. Did I think the book was worth finishing? I'll say yes because the ending, including the epilogue, was practically perfect. There's only one sex scene that is not overly descriptive, but it suits the story just fine. I did have my reservations about that first kiss, and I wonder what some other readers thought about it. The story does have some entertaining sporadic humor, which felt natural and kept the story afloat. </span>
  <a data-text-id="729579941942679138" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


